subSubSection.paragraph:
Amongst these characters, the division of the carpus of pereopod 2 and quite possibly the absence of ventral rostral teeth can readily be used to differentiate the two families, although determination of their polarity is not straightforward. In 
Chlorotocellidae
the pereopod 2 car 
pus
is consistently divided into three articles, whereas in 
Pandalidae
, the number of the carpal articles is quite variable according to taxa, but none are tri-articulate (cf. 
Komai 1994
). The absence of ventral rostral teeth is also reported in three taxa of the pandalid genus 

Plesionika

(
Chace 1985
) but with doubt (see 
Chace 1985
; 
Komai et al. 2005
; 
Hayashi 2009
; 
Komai 2011
; 
Li and Chan 2013
). Such a similarity, if really present, can be resulted from homoplasy (
Liao et al. 2019
).
